		<autolevel level="1">
			<feature>
				<name>Использование заклинаний</name>
				<text>An event in your past, или in the life of a parent или ancestor, left an indelible mark on you, infusing you with arcane magic. This font of magic, whatever its origin, fuels your spells. See chapter 10 for the general rules of Использование заклинаний и chapter 11 for the sorcerer spell list.</text>
				<text />
				<text>Заговоры</text>
				<text>At 1st level, you know four Заговоры of your choice from the sorcerer spell list. You learn an additional sorcerer cantrip of your choice at 4-го level и another at 10th level.</text>
				<text />
				<text>Ячейки заклинаний</text>
				<text>The Sorcerer table shows how many spell slots you have to cast your spells of 1st level и higher. To cast one of these sorcerer spells, you must expend a slot of the spell's level или higher. You regain all expended spell slots when you finish a long rest.</text>
				<text>    For example, if you know the 1st-level spell burning hands и have a 1st-level и a 2nd-level spell slot available, you can cast burning hands using either slot.</text>
				<text />
				<text>Известные заклинания первого и более высоких уровней</text>
				<text>You know two 1st-level spells of your choice from the sorcerer spell list.</text>
				<text>    You learn an additional sorcerer spell of your choice at each level except 12-го, 14th, 16-го, 18-го, 19-го, и 20th. Each of these spells must be of a level for which you have spell slots. For instance, При достижении 3rd level in this class, you can learn one new spell of 1st или 2nd level.</text>
				<text>    Additionally, when you gain a level in this class, you can choose one of the sorcerer spells you know и replace it with another spell from the sorcerer spell list, which also must be of a level for which you have spell slots.</text>
				<text />
				<text>Базовая характеристика заклинаний</text>
				<text>Charisma is your Базовая характеристика заклинаний for your sorcerer spells, since the power of your magic relies on your ability to project your will into the world. You use your Charisma whenever a spell refers to your Базовая характеристика заклинаний. In addition, you use your модификатор Харизмы when setting the saving throw DC for a sorcerer spell you cast и when making an attack roll with one.</text>
				<text>    Сл спасброска = 8 + бонус мастерства + your модификатор Харизмы</text>
				<text>    Модификатор броска атаки = бонус мастерства + your модификатор Харизмы</text>
			</feature>
			<feature>
				<name>Sorcerous Origin</name>
				<text>Choose a sorcerous origin, which describes the source of your innate magical power: Draconic Bloodline, Wild Magic, Favored Soul, или Storm Sorcerer.</text>
				<text>    Your choice grants you features when you choose it at 1st level и again at 6th, 14th, и 18-го level.</text>
			</feature>
			<feature optional="YES">
				<name>Sorcerous Origin: Draconic Bloodline</name>
				<text>Your innate magic comes from draconic magic that was mingled with your blood или that of your ancestors. Most often, sorcerers with this origin trace their descent back to a mighty sorcerer of ancient times who made a bargain with a dragon или who might even have claimed a dragon parent. Some of these bloodlines are well established in the world, but most are obscure. Any given sorcerer could be the first of a new bloodline, as a result of a pact или some other exceptional circumstance.</text>
			</feature>
			<feature optional="YES">
				<name>Sorcerous Origin: Wild Magic</name>
				<text>Your innate magic comes from the wild forces of chaos that underlie the order of creation. You might have endured exposure to some form of raw magic, perhaps through a planar portal leading to Limbo, the Elemental Planes, или the mysterious Far Realm. Perhaps you were blessed by a powerful fey creature или marked by a demon. или your magic could be a fluke of your birth, with no apparent cause или reason. However it came to be, this chaotic magic churns within you, waiting for any outlet.</text>
			</feature>
			<feature optional="YES">
				<name>Sorcerous Origin: Favored Soul</name>
				<text>You have been chosen by a deity, и bestowed with a fragment of their divine power. You have been fundamentally changed by the touch of this deity, which awakens powerful magical abilities inside you</text>
			</feature>
			<feature optional="YES">
				<name>Sorcerous Origin: Storm</name>
				<text>Your innate magic comes from the power of elemental air. Perhaps you were born during a howling gale so powerful that folk still tell stories of it. Your lineage might include the influence of potent air creatures such as vaati или djinni. Whatever the case, the magic of the storm permeates your soul.</text>
				<text />
				<text>Storm sorcerers are invaluable members of a ship's crew. Their magic allows them to exert control over wind и weather in their immediate area. Their abilities also prove useful in repelling attacks by sahuagin, pirates, и other waterborne threats.</text>
			</feature>
			<feature optional="YES">
				<name>Sorcerous Origin: Shadow</name>
				<text>Your innate magic comes from the Shadowfell. You might trace your lineage to an entity from that place, или perhaps you were exposed to its fell energy и transformed in some fundamental manner.</text>
				<text />
				<text>    The power of shadow magic casts a strange pall over your physical presence. The spark of life that sustains you is muffled, as if it struggles to remain viable against the dark energy that imbues your soul. At your option, you can pick from или roll on the following table to create a unique quirk for your character.</text>
				<text />
				<text>d6 - Quirk</text>
				<text>1 — You are always icy cold to the touch.</text>
				<text>2 — When you are asleep, you don't appear to breathe (though you must still breathe to survive).</text>
				<text>3 — You don't seem to bleed, even when badly injured.</text>
				<text>4 — Your heart beats once per minute. This even sometimes surprises you.</text>
				<text>5 — You have trouble remembering that living creatures и corpses should be treated differently.</text>
				<text>6 — You blinked. Once. Last week.</text>
			</feature>
